Colombian president extends condolences to Norway over twin attacks
2011-07-24 04:27:44 GMT
BOGOTA, July 23 (Xinhua) -- Colombian President Juan Manuel Santos on Saturday condemned the twin attacks in Norway, in which at least 92 people were killed.Expressing condolences to the Norwegian people via his official Twitter accout, Santos said his country stands in solidarity with the Norway in fighting terrorism."We must intensify the fight against terrorism on a global scale," said Santos, whose own country has been plagued for decades by organized crime and rebel groups classified as terrorist by his administration.At least seven people were killed in a bombing on Friday in the heart of the Norwegian capital Oslo, and at least 85 people died in a horrific shooting spree two hours later on an island south of Oslo. 
